  "skill_name": "mobile-responsive-design",
  "summary": "Make web apps mobile-responsive with proper breakpoints, touch targets, and layouts",
  "content": "# Mobile-Responsive Design

## When to Use

When building or polishing web apps that need to work on mobile devices. Apply this when:
- Initial build is desktop-only
- Users report mobile usability issues
- Before launching a public-facing product
- Polish tasks mention "mobile" or "responsive"

## Prerequisites

- HTML pages with viewport meta tag: `<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">`
- Existing CSS (inline or external)
- Basic understanding of media queries

## Procedure

### 1. Audit Current Mobile State

Test on mobile viewport or use browser DevTools:
- Resize to 375px (iPhone) and 768px (iPad)
- Check for horizontal scroll, tiny text, cramped layouts
- Note problem areas: navigation, forms, tables, modals, cards

### 2. Add Responsive Breakpoints

Add media queries at common breakpoints:

```css
/* Tablet/Mobile - 768px and below */
@media (max-width: 768px) {
    /* Tablet adjustments */
}

/* Small Mobile - 480px and below */
@media (max-width: 480px) {
    /* Phone adjustments */
}
```

### 3. Fix Navigation

**Desktop sidebar pattern:**
```css
@media (max-width: 768px) {
    .sidebar { display: none; }
    .main-content { margin-left: 0; padding: 20px 16px; }

    /* Add bottom mobile nav */
    .mobile-nav {
        position: fixed;
        bottom: 0;
        left: 0;
        right: 0;
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-around;
        padding: 12px 8px;
    }

    .mobile-nav .nav-item {
        min-width: 44px;
        min-height: 44px;
    }

    .main-content { padding-bottom: 80px; }
}
```

### 4. Make Touch Targets 44px+

All interactive elements need minimum 44px × 44px tap area:

```css
@media (max-width: 768px) {
    .btn { min-height: 44px; padding: 12px 20px; }
    .nav-item { min-height: 44px; padding: 10px; }
    .tab { min-height: 44px; }
}
```

### 5. Fix Form Inputs (iOS Zoom Prevention)

**Critical:** iOS Safari zooms in on inputs with font-size < 16px.

```css
@media (max-width: 768px) {
    .form-input, .form-textarea, select {
        font-size: 16px; /* Prevents iOS zoom */
        padding: 14px 16px;
    }
}
```

### 6. Stack Multi-Column Layouts

Convert grids/flex layouts to single column:

```css
@media (max-width: 768px) {
    .two-col { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .stats-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .form-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
}
```

### 7. Handle Tables

**Option A - Horizontal Scroll:**
```css
@media (max-width: 768px) {
    .table-wrapper {
        overflow-x: auto;
        -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;
    }
    table { min-width: 600px; }
}
```

**Option B - Card Layout** (better UX but more work):
```css
@media (max-width: 768px) {
    table, thead, tbody, tr { display: block; }
    th { display: none; }
    td { 
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        padding: 12px;
    }
    td::before { content: attr(data-label); font-weight: 600; }
}
```

### 8. Full-Screen Modals on Mobile

```css
@media (max-width: 768px) {
    .modal-overlay {
        padding: 0;
        align-items: flex-end; /* Bottom sheet */
    }

    .modal {
        max-width: 100%;
        max-height: 95vh;
        border-radius: 16px 16px 0 0;
    }

    .modal-footer {
        flex-direction: column;
    }

    .modal-footer .btn {
        width: 100%;
    }
}
```

### 9. Reduce Padding & Font Sizes

**Tablet (768px):**
```css
@media (max-width: 768px) {
    .container { padding: 16px 12px; }
    .card { padding: 16px; }
    .page-title { font-size: 1.5rem; }
    h1 { font-size: 2rem; }
}
```

**Small Mobile (480px):**
```css
@media (max-width: 480px) {
    .container { padding: 12px 8px; }
    .card { padding: 12px; }
    .page-title { font-size: 1.25rem; }
    h1 { font-size: 1.75rem; }
}
```

### 10. Test & Iterate

- Test on DevTools mobile viewports
- Check all pages, not just homepage
- Verify: no horizontal scroll, all buttons tappable, text readable
- Test forms: can you type without zoom?

## Common Pitfalls

**Forgetting iOS zoom fix:** Always set `font-size: 16px` on inputs for mobile
**Tiny tap targets:** Buttons/links < 44px are hard to tap accurately
**Horizontal scroll:** Content wider than viewport breaks mobile UX
**Not testing forms:** Desktop forms often break on mobile keyboards
**Modals too small:** Small centered modals are unusable on mobile
**Forgetting bottom nav spacing:** Content gets hidden behind fixed bottom nav

## Quick Wins

1. Add viewport meta tag if missing
2. Set input font-size to 16px on mobile
3. Stack grid layouts to single column
4. Make all buttons min-height: 44px
5. Add mobile navigation (bottom or hamburger)

These 5 fixes solve 80% of mobile usability issues.",
